I am sorry to hear this. :(

maybe software engineering is not your nitch.

You took some pretty good classes so far.

162 is A LOT OF PROGRAMMING with enormous projects. 

so maybe try THEORY OF COMPUTATION or CRYPTOGRAPHY.

they are offered next semester. 

since 188 & 170 are math based you might like these classes.

becasue of the work of Dr.Goldwasser  & Dr. Blum (Turing award winners)


these two areas have research significance.

———

161 is also a fantastic class. So you might like it. it is a go to for many !.

lots of good research potential here too !! For example :: because of the recent Solar winds Hack

———————————-

BEFORE YOU TAKE 189 is important to take EE126 & EE127.

so you check those out too. There are mostly math oriented with some lab components.

Awesome . Thanks for this great advice. I just completely ignored 169A thats why got Np.
Unfortunately i dont think it’s possible for me to likr take both EE126 and EE127 and then take 189( no time) . So i am taking it directly. I will try my best to make sure i understand the material properly. Any advice for me taking 189 without EE127 and EE126.
 In my final semester i think i am gonna take 161 and 162 , after reading these helpful answers . Thanks again

If you're taking 189 in the spring w/ shewchuk, you should be fine. I did not take 126 or 127, and got an A. He reviews a lot of the concepts from those classes in lecture. The only problem you might have is with HW2 (the weeder hw), which has a lot of material from 126 and 127. Just be sure to start that one early and go to OH.
You don't need 126 and 127 for 189, it's not a hard prereq.

There is a class called software engineering .

so maybe that would be good too.

It teaches you the details of how software is developed at companies.

——————

it is VITAL & OF THE UTMOST IMPORTANCE  to take  EE126 & EE127.

Mastery of the material is crucial to take CS189.
